bd4b29ad-059b-4818-9438-a97171e3e68b	64fed17f-e14c-4d95-b107-25c3b42d3e3f	Chris Wesser	# PRE-CALL BRIEF: CHRIS WESSER\n\n## QUICK SUMMARY\nChris is a hot affiliate contact with strong momentum—last call was "fucking awesome." You're moving him into a capital raise advisor role with docs already in progress. Get those docs finalized and locked in.\n\n## COMMUNICATION STYLE\nDirect, enthusiastic, casual language. Match his energy. Skip the formalities.\n\n## AI PERSONALITY ASSESSMENT\nHe's energized and engaged. Keep pace with his momentum—don't over-explain or slow down with unnecessary details.\n\n## KEY ACTION\n**Get commitment on capital raise advisor docs.** Confirm timeline for completion and next steps. Pin down when he can officially start.\n\n---\n\n**BONUS:** Since this is moving fast, ask if there's anything blocking progress on the docs or if he needs anything from you to accelerate.	{"Capital raise advisor — docs in progress","Follow up with Chris Wesser"}	[{"date": "2026-04-04T18:38:27.818Z", "channel": "call_outbound", "summary": "Everything was fucking awesome"}]	2026-04-04 19:03:10.152893+00
84bd344e-359e-49f0-8d8a-9476144217f9	64fed17f-e14c-4d95-b107-25c3b42d3e3f	Chris Wesser	# PRE-CALL BRIEF: Chris Wesser\n\n## 1. QUICK SUMMARY\nChris is a hot affiliate contact with zero friction—last call was "fucking awesome." He's advising on your capital raise and has docs in progress. This is momentum you need to lock in.\n\n## 2. COMMUNICATION STYLE\nCasual, direct, high-energy. Match his enthusiasm. Skip the formalities.\n\n## 3. AI PERSONALITY ASSESSMENT\nHe's already bought in emotionally. Don't over-explain or sell—just move fast and keep the energy up.\n\n## 4. KEY ACTION\n**Get clarity on doc timeline and next milestone.** Ask: "What do you need from me to move this forward?" Then commit to a specific follow-up date.\n\n---\n\n**Note:** Request LinkedIn/company intel from research team before next call—you're flying blind on context.	{"Capital raise advisor — docs in progress","Follow up with Chris Wesser"}	[{"date": "2026-04-04T18:38:27.818Z", "channel": "call_outbound", "summary": "Everything was fucking awesome"}]	2026-04-04 19:15:52.160612+00
bf5e8609-ccc2-4003-855f-92d6ad92b89c	09611d5e-69b9-453c-901b-40aa114f80b5	J. Allen Smith	# PRE-CALL BRIEF: J. Allen Smith\n\n## QUICK SUMMARY\nInstitutional investor at Prudential Real Estate Investors. Warm lead. Purpose: Understand their real estate investment focus and explore potential fit for partnership/investment opportunity.\n\n## COMMUNICATION STYLE\nData-driven institutional investor. Lead with numbers and track record — skip the fluff.\n\n## AI PERSONALITY ASSESSMENT\nExpects you to have done homework. Come prepared with their AUM and specific RE sector info, or you'll lose credibility immediately.\n\n## KEY ACTION\n**STOP — Don't call yet.** Complete the open task first:\n- **Research:** Prudential REI's current AUM + their real estate focus areas (residential, commercial, multifamily, etc.)\n- **Then call** with a specific angle: "I noticed you focus on [sector]. We've had success with [relevant experience]. Worth 15 minutes to explore?"\n\n---\n\n**Once researched, call (415) 291-5020**	{"Research AUM and RE focus before outreach"}	[]	2026-04-05 04:25:31.882057+00
